<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Perl_Module_Changes">Perl Module Changes</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=Operations_Agent:12.10/Perl526Migration&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=1" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" title="Edit section: Perl Module Changes">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=Operations_Agent:12.10/Perl526Migration&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1" title="Edit section: Perl Module Changes">edit source</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<p>With 5.26 upgrade, Perl code modules list has some deprecated modules. However, these modules will still be maintained in CPAN. Perl modules removed from Perl core has been added as additional module in 5.26 version. Hence installation path of few module changes. But this does not have any impact to the "use &lt;module&gt;" construct used in Perl and no changes required from consumers.
</p>
